caption:
Racing has always been a key outlet for @jesswarnerjuddxx. The Olympic 10,000-meter runner loves giving a full effort in workouts and building fitness to see how fast she can be. For Jess, race day is the fun part. That’s when her hard work gets put to the test. 

But after spending years climbing the global ranks on the track, Jess’s ability to run at full strength was suddenly taken from her. Last year, the four-time British champion was diagnosed with epilepsy, a brain condition that causes recurring seizures. 

Though the diagnosis cut her Olympic year short, Jess was able to receive treatment and ultimately return to the sport with a new perspective. Now, she’s racing with more joy and motivation than ever before. Learn about Jess’s incredible comeback on the blog, available to read at the link in bio. 

#FlyHumanFly
